{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect complex multiplication in packed_cmult2 NEON implementation\n\n### Summary\nThe `packed_cmult2` function in the ARM NEON optimized DFT implementation was not performing proper complex multiplication. The function was missing the imaginary components of the first operand, resulting in incorrect FFT computations.\n\nThe bug manifested as incorrect signal processing results in 5G NR downlink when running on ARM-based platforms with NEON optimization enabled. Users reported degraded PDSCH decoding performance and higher BLER under certain channel conditions.\n\nThe issue was in the calculation of the real and imaginary parts of the complex multiplication result. The original implementation only computed partial terms:\n- Real part: `a.real * b.real` (missing `- a.imag * b.imag`)\n- Imaginary part: `a.real * b.imag` (missing `+ a.imag * b.real`)\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts_neon.c`: Fixed `packed_cmult2` to perform complete complex multiplication using `vmlsl_s16` and `vmlal_s16` intrinsics to compute all required terms.\n\n"
}